name: r-rerddap
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.8.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rerddap
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rerddap_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rerddap/rerddap_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: da47ec2afe6a8d9cc02989df49d982152e070720f65897e4ac5087babc5ad549

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-crul >=0.7.4
    - r-data.table >=1.12.0
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr >=0.5.0
    - r-hoardr >=0.5.2
    - r-jsonlite >=1.6
    - r-ncdf4 >=1.16
    - r-tibble
    - r-xml2 >=1.2.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-crul >=0.7.4
    - r-data.table >=1.12.0
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr >=0.5.0
    - r-hoardr >=0.5.2
    - r-jsonlite >=1.6
    - r-ncdf4 >=1.16
    - r-tibble
    - r-xml2 >=1.2.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rerddap')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rerddap')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropensci/rerddap
  license: MIT
  summary: "General purpose R client for 'ERDDAP' servers. Includes functions to search for 'datasets', get summary information on 'datasets', and fetch 'datasets', in either 'csv' or 'netCDF' format. 'ERDDAP' information: <https://upwell.pfeg.noaa.gov/erddap/information.html>."
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ocefpaf
